==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Culvers root
<hw>Cul"ver's root`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <ety>[So called after a
Dr. <etsep>Culver</etsep>, who used it.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The root of a handsome erect herb (<spn>Leptandra Virginica</spn>
syn. <spn>Veronica Virginica</spn>) common in most moist woods of North
America , used as an active cathartic and emetic; also, the plant
itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Culvert</ent>⟦br⟧
